caption: Delicious Thai food! The lunch special is an amazing deal!
Heard great reviews and ordered but below average food. Their lunch menu is good value but the flavor, taste is underwhelming compared to other Thai places.

We ordered delivery. It took an hour and a half to be delivered. When it arrived half of the food was cold. The order was messed up and as you can see from the pics. The food was not very temping either. The Shrimp Rolls hardly had any shrimp in them and the ones that did had the tails one. Plus they were soggy and tough to eat. There are a lot of Thai places in the area. We will not be ordering from this one again.

Ordered the pad thai, pot stickers, and tom yum soup. The pad thai was bland, really lacked the sweet and sour taste you want, and the noodles overcooked. The soup was pretty good and the pot stickers had a good consistency but lacked flavor as well.
Delicious pad Thai done with lots of flavor! I like it bc it’s not too sweet which I find some lower quality to taste like

I went here because it was recommended and reviews were pretty good. I was definitely not impressed. I got the Pad Thai and potstickers and egg roll. Pad Thai had no flavor and the veggies weren’t great. Egg rolls were tough. I probably wouldn’t eat here again.

Ordered tofu pad Thai with potsticker and a Tom yum soup. The potstickers were amazing. But the noodles and soup were bland. Noodles tasted slightly sweet and sour from the lime but that's it. Soup was fresh and aromatic but not spicy at all. The portion size was good though. Will try pad see ew with beef and potstickers next time.
Great proportions for the price. Love this place. Local staple.
Authentic, succulent, delicious Thai cuisine!
Real damn good!
Crispy curry rice salad was greasy and neither one of us liked it. The pad thai was okay. The menu was confusing online vs what they really offered in person.

Silli Kori never disappoints. It’s simply upscale, well executed Thai food, regardless if you take out or eat in. Very nice staff as well. I routinely drive 30+ minutes for their food because it’s just that good.

The best lunch special in town- $9 for an entree (huge!) and appetizer (love their veggie tempura and potstickers. I got the Kee Mow (drunken noodles) with BBQ pork added. The food here is just excellent, and service is fast and friendly. Come here for lunch and a drink, you won’t regret it.
Such great food!!
thai food and the feeling at this spot is very good. Super appetizing. There was fast and courteous service.
Everything is incredible

We miss dining here in person but the take out / delivery is just as amazing. Ordered the crispy rice salad and pineapple duck curry - one bite and we were transported to our trip to Thailand in the same way the critic in Ratatouille relives his childhood through one bite. No joke. It always come hot, fresh and fast. It’s become our go to place for Thai delivery.
Great food at a decent price! I work close to Silli Kori and order from them often. Whether I order delivery or pick-up, my food is always correct and available quickly!

Tasty Siamese snacks! My papaya salad was delish! My chicken pad Thai was definitely delicious! The red curry beef dish was awesome! The brightness of the flavors is so yummy! Like the dipping sauce for those amazing little egg rolls! Wow!
Fast service, tasty food. Drinks could be a bit stronger.
Great lunch combo a d equal price to match.  Huge selection and fun options.

This place should just be Silly Kori, we ordered the udon noodles, pad Thai, and pepper beef for pick up during covid-19. All the food had lackluster flavor, as well as small servings of everything (though the servings are always forgiven when the flavor is fantastic). By and large, not a great experience, perhaps some of it was due to them having to crank out a lot of orders as they did seem busy. I trulydtruly not plan on going back.
My favorite Thai in Chicago, with reasonable prices and an attractive space as well. A great hidden gem!
This place is great. Super friendly service with super delicious food!

I come to this excellent place often  as I love the  special atmosphere that is part of this restaurant. The team is awfuly helpful and qualified. The service is very efficient. Also, the food they serve is perfect. I have been there often and I was always satisfied. The expense is fair. I highly suggest this restaurant to to all.

This place is my go-to. It is excellent food in a clean environment at a good price. The kao soi is a particular favorite of mine: a generous bowl of noodles, fried noodles, sour greens, and braised beef in a rich curry broth. Love it.

Impressed!  Good dinner vibes and lovely food. The ambiance was soft and the noise level was very quiet which was awesome.  I was able to enjoy my conversation with my delicious green curry pasta.  I would like to see more items on their menu though. Could do without the random Japanese YouTube videos playing on their tv because it doesn’t work with the vibe and it’s distracting. Service was attentive and friendly. Will be back again!
really cool interior. really friendly and warm staff.  amazing fresh food. great vibrant taste. really great food. will def be back to try some of their other menus.
The food is delicious. Pad Thai, lettuce wraps, kee mow, pot stickers, yellow curry, beef skewers, and every app we had was fresh and flavorful. A gem!
Fantastic and flavorful food, I like the mood this spot has, and the employees were welcoming. Will definitely visit here again.
Unfortunately, the food is too greasy! Make sure you keep drinking water while your eating and after you finish. If you're thinking of dining in, just get any dessert.
Awesome thai restaurant.  The avocado tempura starter is a must try. Entree menu is also great. Service was good and prices are great.
Solid menu and prices.
Not a lot of vegetarian options. Otherwise, great spot. Good service.
good food rude service.
Love this place -- they have a really great lunch special too! Pad Thai and crispy salad are among my favorites.
Fresh, delicious food.  Really enjoyed the ambiance here.  There’s a large patio that you should take advantage of while the weather is still nice.
Wonderful food and service. Our party of 3 ordered three appetizers, pad Thai, and Kori's favorite noodle which was spectacular. This is a gem in the popular Wicker Park area.
Love this place. Good ambiance, great food, nice patio space, and awesome delivery too! It's definitely our favorite Thai spot in the neighborhood!
I love the red and green curries, I could eat this everyday. They also have great lunch specials and it's a great place to bring a date.
If I could go here everyday I would. The staff probably get tired of seeing me but they are nice to me every single time. Now they remember my order! I recommend this place to everyone.

Been to this place twice, and had extremely positive experiences both times. First, ate at the restaurant- the ambiance was awesome, food is good, and not too expensive. Got take-out tonight, which may have been even more impressive. The egg rolls were tasty, crunchy, and came with a good honey sauce. My pad thai had a good amount of chicken in it. The portion size was just about right. This place slaps. Pics were my Grubhub order, total was 26 bucks.
I dropped an earring back and the staff went the extra mile to find it for me! Amazing service and food!

My husband and I went here based on the reviews and we were blown away by how good the food was! It is honestly the best Thai food we've ever had, and we eat Thai food a lot. We could not figure out why there wasn't a wait...so strange. We really hope this place stays around for a long time, especially since we just moved to the hood. I got the Massaman Curry and my husband got the Kao Soi. Great service and the atmosphere is awesome too. Love that you can sit outside in the summer.

The kao soi is different from the version I had in Chiang Mai, Thailand in that it was a nutty curry rather than red, the meat was in chunks rather than minced, and there were crunchy stuff on top which I think is an american thing. But I'm not complaining. I took off the crunchy stuff and the rest of it was very delicious. Also note that the pork belly is actually pork skewers.
Wow, amazing find. Will definitely come back. We both had a salmon which was delicious. Portions are generous, great presentation, inexpensive, and atmosphere romantic.

This place delivers exactly what it should. It's a Thai joint in the middle of wicker. Do not expect the most authentic tasting dishes. It caters to the palate of the locals.  Now that said, the food is exceptional. We got the pad Thai and the Kao Soi. If you've ever had other Thai food in this city you can tell if the restaurant skimps on some of their ingredients when you order these dishes.  For example the beef in the Kao Soi we're not thin slices of skirt. The Pad Thai uses actual nuts instead of paste.  Expect an Western take of Thai flavors and you won't be disappointed. It's what you wish your take out tasted like. 100% would recommend.
Nice area. Foods are delicious.
Great place
Interesting food very different and tasty spices unique and the mango scallops amazing 😍

Just visited for first time for lunch. The prices are extremely reasonable especially since it includes an appetizer like crab rangoon or cucumber salad. The son in law eggs is a must try dish. I cannot wait to visit again soon.

We do not ever order delivery but it was so freezing cold in Chicago there was no way we were leaving the house. The experience was both painful and funny as we attempted to get our food in the house. The delivery guy just could not figure out how to ring our bell. He could not even open our door after we buzzed him in several times. As we watched this comedy of errors through our video screen, he called us on his phone. I assumed this call would fix our problems but it turned into a task because the driver was speaking broken English. For a minute, I thought we might not get our food even though it was outside our front door.  After much direction, we finally got the delivery guy in and he delivered our food. We got crispy rolls with ground chicken and vermicelli. The dish was beautifully presented for delivery food. The rolls were sliced and topped with cilantro and carrots. They were good but the rolls could have used a dipping sauce on the side. That's an issue with delivery. Did we actually get everything for our dish.  We also ordered a hot and a mild version of Kee Mow Noodles with chicken, wide noodle, tomatoes, vegetables, carrots, onions, basil, bean sprouts and a sweet soy sauce. The dishes were good. I was very unhappy because my noodles were stuck together.  Again this can be a causality of delivery and this is why we avoid delivery always.  The dish was also a little too sweet for my taste buds. I like a true balance of flavors in my food.  I'd like to dine at thr restaurant and have the dishes served fresh. I will say that the delivery was fast and arrived earlier then promised including the drivers mishaps. We have not ordered delivery in over 10 years and it was nice to not go out in the freezing cold to get out food. I was also let down they didn't send any chop sticks. Asian food doesn't taste good to me with a plastic fork which is what they actually sent. Luckily I have a spare set of chop sticks in the house to enjoy my food. I'm ready for culinary emergencies.

When I first arrived, I was worried the upscale atmosphere would translate to small, pretentious plates or high prices. Neither was true! The menu is short and doesn't have much in the way of customization, but the servings are hearty and the two dishes we tried were delicious. The craft cocktail menu is especially delicious and very reasonably priced. A jewel-like surprise!

Cute space, trendy atmosphere. The pad Thai is ok - I have a gluten allergy so there was not much else to eat. The server seemed annoyed that I had all these allergies and we felt very rushed. I'm surprised that for a restaurant on Division St they weren't more accommodating for allergies.
Good food, good service
Yummy food and good service

We have always loved Silli Kori. Recently they opened a sushi bar in the back of the restaurant called Kave. It is a very good addition to the neighborhood. Very artfully designed and presented plates that are delicious. They even give you a free sample while you are deciding on the menu. The staff is friendly and attentive. Reasonably priced and   comfortable atmosphere make it a go to treat.
Delicious!
excellent service. The scallop sushi was terrific. Cant reccomend highly enough

Good Thai food with good drinks! The pad Thai was different with the omelet top which added a layer of unexpected texture to the bite, and with good flavor. The kao soi was very bland. The drink was good and the service pleasant. Metered or free street parking, credit accepted, reservation recommended.

My friend and I went on a Wednesday night for dinner. The was no wait, but still pretty busy for a week night. The decor is nice and simple without being cheap or cheesy. We ordered the scallops for appetizer, Pad Thai noodles with shrimp, and Kao Soi. I also ordered the Bangkok mule. The drink was delicious. The scallops dish was refreshing, and were cooked perfectly. The Pad Thai was very good too. However, the Kao Soi was very bland. We added chili sauce to it, but that didn't really help either. Our server was very friendly. I will be back to try more dishes.
The food was ok
Amaaazing food. The bar is made out of a bowling alley lane?! Terrific decor and staff. It's all custom. It's all been thought out. Super fresh and fantastic.
Excellent food!! I’ve traveled extensively in Thailand, and the taste here took me back. Excellent service!! You really can’t beat the lunch specials either. Will be back for sure.

Some of the best Asian Fusion food I’ve had. Great atmosphere, the staff was very friendly and the food was just amazing. What stood out was the tuna poke and the spicy scallop roll. From the first bite, I could immediately tell the tuna was one of the best quality you can find. I asked the chef and sure enough, they serve bluefin tuna. Amazing! Get one of their signature rolls. The spicy scallop was outstanding. Extremely fresh and a perfect combination of flavors. Good variety of wines! This has just become one of my favorite spots in Chicago!
First visit, very impressed will return (HUGE CRAWFISH)
Loved the food and the spice I recommend u visit and have a meal at this place They have exceed my expectations of Thai Food.
Very nice

From my wife after we got the check - “You can just tell it is better quality then anything out there in Chicago.”  I would 100% agree. This was amazing and tasted better than I remember my time in Thailand. You’ll love it!
Get the salmon!
Food was cold. To fix all they did was put it under a braiser. Came out with the same squeezed lime and very wilted cilantro. Very poor. Walked out
I love this place!
Awesome Thai place with good quality food for a good price and nice drinks!
Yum!  Fabulous food, ambiance and value! Great meal!
The menu was interesting the people were great and I loved it and the food tremendously good
Great Thai in a quiet setting.
Curry was outstanding and the service was so friendly I am still smiling
I order faithfully they are quick and amazing! Pad Thai is a must and Thai ice tea is delishhhh love them!

I love this place. Food is delicious and not too expensive. I think they lowered their prices a bit - I remember going there right after they remodeled, and it was way too pricey then. The painting on the wall is very cool too.

I usually get takeout, but recently brought some out of town guests here to dine in. It was quick service and everyone loved their food. Minus one star because it's a more limited menu than most Thai restaurants.
Curry!
Stylish decor, and satisfying thai tucked right off division in wicker Park
My favorite Thai Restaurant in Chicago. The ambiance is quiet and private, the food amazing and the staff wonderful. I highly recommend for lunch.
What a hidden gem.  This place is right on division street. Extremely generous portions, friendly service. Nice cozy little place.
We ate at the restaurant and the food was really great! We had the Kao Soi and Kori's Noodles. Both were delicious, fresh and we will definitely be going back to try other things on the menu!
Good Thai food and appetizers, atmosphere is nice and laid back.
Great atmosphere, fantastic dinner.
I have eaten here probably a dozen times and everything I’ve had tasted amazing. Chicken wild rice soup is one of my favorites. Beef Pad Thai does not disappoint!!
The best!!!!!
Good food/drink options and friendly staff. However, service is terribly slow even on nights that aren't very busy.
Great atmosphere and amazing food! Our go to's are the pad Thai, salmon, and sesame chicken.
Have been looking for  a good Thai place in the neighborhood and finally found it! Me and my gf have been back 10+ times since we found it 2 months ago and it is amazing every time.

I get takeout from here often. The food is fresh, with lots of veggies. Takeout orders are put together quickly and accurately, and staff is friendly. They have plenty of vegetarian options, as well. If you eat in, there's a bar and a nice set of cocktail options, as well. Great neighborhood staple.
Solid local thai place and the Cousine Bar sign in front makes me laugh every time.
The grilled salmon with baby bok choy and pineapple salsa is the best!
Beautiful design, very friendly staff and delicious vegetarian Tom Kha and Green Curry
A hidden gem. Great food, drinks and staff.
Great thai food at a very fair price.
Food and service is great and fast. Awesome lunch special selections

Note this is no longer Thai Village. Older reviews are for an earlier establishment.  The food and service here are both good. It aims for something a little more experimental or upcale than standard Thai fare, but the prices remain reasonable for what's offered. Atmosphere is a sort of rustic minimalism, but still cozy. I've dined here half a dozen times so far and always been satisfied. The Thai dishes have enough kick, ingredients taste fresh, and you can get authentic fish sauce on the side if you ask for it. The bar also serves an impressive cocktail menu.
Excellent lunch menu
Wow! The flavor here is top notch. Rich and Spicy! You definitely need to come try this delicious Thai Food. You can sit on their sidewalk tables and enjoy Division St. while eating delicious food.
classic Thai food w a contemporary/wicker park  (including the prices). better atmosphere than other, similar pace, which is what differentiates this spot from similar ones in the area.
Best Pad Thai!

Great food and excellent service. Perfect portions for price. I was so impressed with the  culinary styling and tasty drinks. The friendly and patient staff just add to the simple yet stylish atmosphere. This place is wonderful and I would highly recommend planning a visit.
So good ^___^
I ordered crab Rangoon chicken pad Thai and chicken/rice soup. Everything was delicious and delivered on time! Will be going back for sure
Great food, good prices!
Just ordered via grub hub...honestly the best authentic Thai I have had since I can remember. Order Thai spicy!!!!!
Only have ordered the lunch special, which is an amazing deal. Its a soup, appetizer and main for about $7. Very solid thai, considering there are so many options, especially for that price!
great thai place!! they have amazing lunch specials and the food is authentic!! i bring people here all the time! they also have a great patio in the summer too!!
What's not to love? Great lunch specials! Try the tomato beef lunch special or come outside and eat on the great patio.
the food is just amazing, very traditional thai food, love the place, and the service is good, definitely i'll come back
Thai Village is a great restaurant for fast, reasonable, and good Thai food.  The Thai Iced Tea is delicious, and I recommend the cucumber salad. I usually order the pad thai.

Went there to redeem an expired groupon. Placed an order to go. Ordered the lettuce peanut app, carrott cake. Both were great. I also order the crab wonton app, which they forgot to include but when I called them after I got home and told them about this, they took my name and said that I could get two free apps the next time I came in.

My family and I went to get the lunch special and it was so fullfilling. A lot of food for not a lot. There was an appetizer, soup and a main entree for maybe less than 10 dollars. I really liked this spot.
Nice decor, good food. And.. Excellent prices!

How in god's name did this place get a Bib Gourmand endorsement? I mean, it's not bad... serviceable Thai close to my house, but it's not even the best place in a 3-block radius. I'm baffled. Michelin Man, you got some splainin' to do. The food is mediocre and the service is bad. It used to be byob, that's over now, bummer. Forget about leftovers unless you dig wilty cabbage in every dish. It is cheap, so there's a positive.

I really liked this place. It fades away with its decor compared to other restaurants in the area, but the food and service was excellent. I think Zagat needs to raise their rating. Its really good food.

Exceptionally bland and awful pad thai. I guess I thought that a signature dish like this would be at least palatable anywhere, but I must be wrong. Ups for the crab rangoons, but the rest of the items I've tried here have been just awful and the service, slow. I doubt anyone would go here if there were any decent Thai options in the Wicker Park area. Yuck. Avoid- go to Argyle street, even though it's far away- there are frozen dinners better than this place.
Service was abysmal, server was not attentive and made several mistakes. Have been going there for over a decade and it was never this poor.
